members.member:
      Trims the current image, removing blank space around the edges. 




            Generally, this command is used for automatically 
            trimming blank space from the edges of scanned documents.



            Nevertheless, because this command uses changes in 
            intensity to detect blank space, it can trim edges of any color or 
            intensity.



            If a region is defined for the image, the region 
            is also trimmed if necessary.



            This command supports 12 and 16-bit grayscale and 48 and 64-bit color images. Support for 12 and 16-bit grayscale and 48 and 64-bit color images is available only in the Document/Medical toolkits.



            This command does not support signed data images.



            This command does not support 32-bit grayscale images.


            For more information, refer to Introduction to Image Processing With LEADTOOLS.



Run the  on an image and then AutoCrops the image.
