      Converts a signed image to unsigned. 




            The image may contain negative pixel values and 
            LEADTOOLS will paint/process the image incorrectly.  To use this image 
            correctly the negative pixels should be converted, if it contains 
            negative pixels (if  is True).



            If the  is set to True, this method
            will shift the color values in the image according to Type property.



            The method will also update the  and  
            properties of the .



            .



            This method supports 12 and 16-bit grayscale and 48 
            and 64-bit color images. Support for 12 and 16-bit grayscale and 48 and 
            64-bit color images is available only in the Document/Medical toolkits.



            This command does not support 32-bit grayscale images.


            For more information, refer to Introduction to Image Processing With LEADTOOLS.



Run the  on an image. The passed image must be signed image.
