      Removes speckles from an image. Typically, this command is used to clean up scanned images (such as FAX images).  This command is available in the Document/Medical Toolkits. 




            This command removes 1-pixel speckles, and shrinks some larger speckles. Therefore, in some cases, larger speckles can be completely removed by running it more than once.



            This command supports 12 and 16-bit grayscale and 48 and 64-bit color images. Support for 12 and 16-bit grayscale and 48 and 64-bit color images is available only in the Document/Medical toolkits.



            This command does not support 32-bit grayscale images.


            For more information, refer to Removing Noise.


            In Silverlight and Windows Phone versions of LEADTOOLS, this image processing 
            command will fail if the image data for the RasterImage object is stored internally
             using a Silverlight WriteableBitmap object.  For more information,
            refer to Image Processing Command Limitations in Silverlight.


