      Gets the window center and the window width, if the LookupTable stored inside the 
            image is linear. If the LookupTable stored inside the image is not linear, the 
            command will fail. 




            Pay attention to lookup tables for signed images. 
            The upper half should contain negative values and the lower half should contain 
            positive values.



            This class supports 12 and 16-bit grayscale images. Support for 12 and 16-bit grayscale images is available only in the Document/Medical toolkits.



            This command does not support 32-bit grayscale images.



In Silverlight and Windows Phone versions of LEADTOOLS, this image processing 
            command will fail if the image data for the RasterImage object is stored internally
             using a Silverlight WriteableBitmap object.  For more information,
            refer to Image Processing Command Limitations in Silverlight.



Run the  on the image. and checks the linearity of the LookupTable and computes its window width and center by using this method.
           Public Sub GetLinearVoiLookupTableCommandExample()
